This paper involves the use of reinforcement learning to learn optimal control policies in systems where action space is defined by sentences in natural language. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the development of a library for universal access to different text games, which could fall under the sub-categories of Computation and Language (cs.CL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper also involves testing the generalization and transfer learning performance of the text game playing agent, which could fall under the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
